senses.sense_definition: A female given name of Hebrew origin.

examples.text: My friend <w>Naomi</w> is coming to the party tonight.
They decided to name their new baby daughter <w>Naomi</w>.

senses.sense_definition: A female given name of Japanese origin.

examples.text: <w>Naomi</w> Osaka is a very famous professional tennis player.
She wrote her name, <w>Naomi</w>, using traditional Japanese characters.

senses.sense_definition: The mother-in-law of Ruth in the Bible.

examples.text: In the biblical story, Ruth refused to leave <w>Naomi</w> behind.
After the famine ended, <w>Naomi</w> returned to Bethlehem with her daughter-in-law.
